# Vulnerability Management Lifecycle

## 1. Asset Discovery
Identify assets within the organization.

## 2. Vulnerability Identification
Perform authenticated and unauthenticated scans.

## 3. Risk Assessment
Evaluate severity using CVSS and business impact.

## 4. Prioritization
Focus on critical and exploitable vulnerabilities.

## 5. Remediation
Coordinate with infrastructure and application teams.

## 6. Validation
Rescan assets and verify remediation.

## 7. Reporting
Provide dashboards and executive reports.

# CVSS Overview

CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System) is used to measure the severity of vulnerabilities.

## Severity Ratings

- Critical: 9.0 - 10.0
- High: 7.0 - 8.9
- Medium: 4.0 - 6.9
- Low: 0.1 - 3.9

## Why CVSS Matters

Helps prioritize remediation efforts and security resources.
